Larson Awards Florida Tourism Hall of Fame Meeting Notices Careers Media News Releases Public Records Member Biography You are here: Home About Us Who We Are Florida Council of Tourism Leaders Member Biography Walter Banks Title: President Organization: Lago Mar Beach Resort and Club Committee Position: Member Walter Banks is the owner of Lago Mar Resort and Club in Fort Lauderdale, FL. In 2003, he was named as Florida "Hotelier of the Year" and has also received the Excalibur Award which is the top business award in Broward County. Banks served as Chairman of the VISIT FLORIDA Board of Directors and Vice Chair of Florida Commission on Tourism. In December of 2011, he concluded his term on the Federal Board of Miami, a Branch of the Federal Reserve Bank of Atlanta. Keymmunity, a vital aspect of the Florida District program, empowers District Executives and Lieutenant Governors to oversee monthly reports and communicate with clubs through the completion of Officer Information Forms (OIFs). Access is limited to club presidents, secretaries, and advisors. It ensures efficient and confidential communication channels while strengthening collaboration and accountability within the district, fostering a cohesive and effective leadership network.
